{"type":"message","id":"cf97f184","parentId":"c487273f","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:29:21.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Processing Documentation Files**\n\nI've located `github_documentation.json` within the `docs_archive/` directory, and I'm gearing up to convert it. My plan is to read its contents, transform it into a markdown file (tentatively named `GITHUB_API.md`), and subsequently transfer it to the `legacy_json` directory.\n\n\n**Revising the Conversion Plan**\n\nI'm amending my strategy. Having confirmed `github_documentation.json`'s presence, I'll now convert it. I'll read and transform the JSON contents into a Markdown file, likely `GITHUB_API.md`. Crucially, I'll then move the original JSON to the `legacy_json` directory. This aligns with the 'docs_archive/*.json' instruction.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771151361567_320","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/github_documentation.json"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":11673,"output":205,"cacheRead":8850,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11878,"cost":{"input":0.023346,"output":0.00246,"cacheRead":0.00177,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.027576}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771151355869}}
{"type":"message","id":"80847de0","parentId":"cf97f184","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:29:21.592Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771151361567_320","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"app_name\": \"arkadiy-bot-manager\",\n  \"role\": \"The GitHub App acts as a dedicated identity for the bot within the GitHub ecosystem. Unlike Personal Access Tokens (PATs) which are tied to a specific user, a GitHub App is its own entity with fine-grained permissions.\",\n  \"requirements\": {\n    \"App ID\": \"Unique identifier for the GitHub App.\",\n    \"Installation ID\": \"Specific ID for the account/organization where the app is installed.\",\n    \"Private Key\": \".pem file used to sign JWTs for authentication.\",\n    \"Client Secret\": \"Used for server-to-server interactions (optional for basic bot operations).\"\n  },\n  \"benefits\": [\n    \"Higher rate limits: 5000 requests/hour (vs 60/hour for unauthenticated or basic PAT).\",\n    \"Fine-grained permissions: Only grant access to specific repositories and actions.\",\n    \"Check Run status reporting: Allows the bot to report build/test status directly on PRs.\",\n    \"Improved security: Credentials are tied to the app, not a human user account.\"\n  ]\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771151361590}}
{"type":"message","id":"14927fd3","parentId":"80847de0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:29:28.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing the JSON Content**\n\nI'm currently processing the contents of `docs_archive/github_documentation.json`. My strategy is to transform it into a consistent, structured Markdown document. The target output is `docs_archive/GITHUB_APP.md`, and I'm focusing on incorporating a Table of Contents to start.\n\n\n**Defining the Document Outline**\n\nI'm solidifying the structure for the Markdown output. The Table of Contents is in place. Next up: an Overview section, followed by Authentication/Requirements, and then Benefits. I plan to archive the original JSON to a `legacy_json` directory once I'm done.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771151368533_321","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# GitHub App Integration Reference\n\n## Table of Contents\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Authentication & Requirements](#authentication--requirements)\n- [Benefits](#benefits)\n\n## Overview\n**App Name:** `arkadiy-bot-manager`\n\nThe GitHub App acts as a dedicated identity for the bot within the GitHub ecosystem. Unlike Personal Access Tokens (PATs) which are tied to a specific user, a GitHub App is its own entity with fine-grained permissions.\n\n## Authentication & Requirements\n*   **App ID:** Unique identifier for the GitHub App.\n*   **Installation ID:** Specific ID for the account/organization where the app is installed.\n*   **Private Key:** `.pem` file used to sign JWTs for authentication.\n*   **Client Secret:** Used for server-to-server interactions (optional for basic bot operations).\n\n## Benefits\n*   **Higher Rate Limits:** 5000 requests/hour (vs 60/hour for unauthenticated or basic PAT).\n*   **Fine-Grained Permissions:** Only grant access to specific repositories and actions.\n*   **Check Run Status:** Allows the bot to report build/test status directly on PRs.\n*   **Improved Security:** Credentials are tied to the app, not a human user account.\n","file_path":"docs_archive/GITHUB_APP.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771151368662_322","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mv docs_archive/github_documentation.json docs_archive/legacy_json/"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12105,"output":410,"cacheRead":8913,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12515,"cost":{"input":0.02421,"output":0.00492,"cacheRead":0.0017826,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0309126}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771151361592}}
